00:00:25.454 --> 00:00:26.370 align:middle line:90%
>>GREGG BRADEN: Hello.

00:00:26.370 --> 00:00:27.960 align:middle line:10%
My name's Gregg
Braden, and I'd like

00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:30.750 align:middle line:10%
to be the first to
welcome you to this very

00:00:30.750 --> 00:00:35.670 align:middle line:10%
special presentation of "Missing
Links: Simulation by Design:

00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:38.880 align:middle line:10%
Are We Living in a
Virtual Reality?"

00:00:38.880 --> 00:00:40.920 align:middle line:84%
I am your host for
this entire series,

00:00:40.920 --> 00:00:43.140 align:middle line:84%
and I'm absolutely thrilled
to personally bring

00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:46.650 align:middle line:84%
each and every episode of this
all new "Missing Links" program

00:00:46.650 --> 00:00:48.040 align:middle line:90%
directly to you.

00:00:48.040 --> 00:00:51.180 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to know
why I'm so excited.

00:00:51.180 --> 00:00:54.190 align:middle line:84%
There's a growing body
of scientific evidence

00:00:54.190 --> 00:00:55.980 align:middle line:84%
that now suggests
that we are living

00:00:55.980 --> 00:01:01.110 align:middle line:84%
our lives inside of a digital
simulation, a massive computer

00:01:01.110 --> 00:01:05.370 align:middle line:84%
program the size of the universe
that began running long, long

00:01:05.370 --> 00:01:07.710 align:middle line:84%
ago, sometime in
our ancient past,

00:01:07.710 --> 00:01:11.700 align:middle line:84%
creating the virtual reality
we see as our everyday world

00:01:11.700 --> 00:01:12.980 align:middle line:90%
right now.

00:01:12.980 --> 00:01:16.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, the implications of such
a discovery, they're huge,

00:01:16.420 --> 00:01:18.210 align:middle line:84%
they're vast, they're
deep, and they

00:01:18.210 --> 00:01:22.200 align:middle line:84%
tear right into the core of
our most intimate beliefs

00:01:22.200 --> 00:01:24.840 align:middle line:84%
about everything from
healing and disease

00:01:24.840 --> 00:01:29.100 align:middle line:84%
to war and peace, life, death,
religion, god, angels, ETs,

00:01:29.100 --> 00:01:32.420 align:middle line:84%
aliens, UFOs, the
cosmos, and even beyond.

00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:35.790 align:middle line:84%
Now I know that the possibility
itself may sound like something

00:01:35.790 --> 00:01:37.740 align:middle line:90%
from a science fiction movie.

00:01:37.740 --> 00:01:40.650 align:middle line:84%
And I know that because
it did to me as well.

00:01:40.650 --> 00:01:44.200 align:middle line:84%
That is, until I began to
consider the new evidence.

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:46.530 align:middle line:84%
And that's what this
series is all about.

00:01:46.530 --> 00:01:49.710 align:middle line:84%
In this program we'll
explore the discoveries,

00:01:49.710 --> 00:01:52.090 align:middle line:84%
where they lead, what
they mean in our lives,

00:01:52.090 --> 00:01:53.620 align:middle line:90%
what they're telling us today.

00:01:53.620 --> 00:01:56.790 align:middle line:84%
So let's begin at the beginning
with what scientists are now

00:01:56.790 --> 00:01:59.940 align:middle line:90%
calling the forbidden question.

00:01:59.940 --> 00:02:03.630 align:middle line:84%
Is it possible that each moment
of every day of our lives

00:02:03.630 --> 00:02:07.740 align:middle line:84%
is actually happening inside of
a simulated reality that looks

00:02:07.740 --> 00:02:10.080 align:middle line:90%
and feels totally real to us?

00:02:10.080 --> 00:02:15.850 align:middle line:90%


00:02:15.850 --> 00:02:19.870 align:middle line:84%
First, I'd like to be
absolutely clear about precisely

00:02:19.870 --> 00:02:23.260 align:middle line:84%
what a simulation is, what
I'm talking about when

00:02:23.260 --> 00:02:25.730 align:middle line:90%
I refer to a simulation.

00:02:25.730 --> 00:02:28.900 align:middle line:84%
A simulation is
an experience that

00:02:28.900 --> 00:02:32.900 align:middle line:84%
allows us to immerse ourselves
in an unfamiliar environment,

00:02:32.900 --> 00:02:33.700 align:middle line:90%
first.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And second, it allows us
to master the parameters

00:02:38.050 --> 00:02:41.710 align:middle line:84%
of that environment in
a relatively safe way

00:02:41.710 --> 00:02:44.230 align:middle line:84%
while minimizing
the risk of injury

00:02:44.230 --> 00:02:46.600 align:middle line:90%
to ourselves or to one another.

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:49.180 align:middle line:84%
So the idea of a
digital environment

00:02:49.180 --> 00:02:51.370 align:middle line:84%
is certainly nothing
new for us today.

00:02:51.370 --> 00:02:53.500 align:middle line:84%
We already use
simulated environments

00:02:53.500 --> 00:02:55.340 align:middle line:90%
in a number of places.

00:02:55.340 --> 00:02:57.940 align:middle line:10%
For example, what you're
seeing on your screen

00:02:57.940 --> 00:03:00.940 align:middle line:10%
right now is a
musical awards show.

00:03:00.940 --> 00:03:03.820 align:middle line:10%
It was actually hosted
in Orlando, Florida,

00:03:03.820 --> 00:03:06.730 align:middle line:10%
and the woman that you're
seeing standing on the left

00:03:06.730 --> 00:03:09.700 align:middle line:10%
is the host, is the
emcee of the program.

00:03:09.700 --> 00:03:14.440 align:middle line:10%
And she's presenting an award to
two musicians who could not be

00:03:14.440 --> 00:03:17.080 align:middle line:10%
present at the actual ceremony.

00:03:17.080 --> 00:03:21.490 align:middle line:10%
Because of schedules, they are
performing in London, England.

00:03:21.490 --> 00:03:23.690 align:middle line:10%
Now the audience
didn't know that.

00:03:23.690 --> 00:03:27.940 align:middle line:10%
So you're seeing a holographic
projection, a virtual reality

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:32.560 align:middle line:10%
of those two performers as
if they are live on stage

00:03:32.560 --> 00:03:33.970 align:middle line:10%
with the emcee.

00:03:33.970 --> 00:03:35.710 align:middle line:84%
And as you see on
your screen, it's

00:03:35.710 --> 00:03:38.270 align:middle line:84%
very difficult to tell that
they are not actually there.

00:03:38.270 --> 00:03:41.140 align:middle line:84%
The audience didn't know that
these people were not really

00:03:41.140 --> 00:03:41.950 align:middle line:90%
there.

00:03:41.950 --> 00:03:45.040 align:middle line:84%
And it was from
this digital reality

00:03:45.040 --> 00:03:47.230 align:middle line:84%
that the two were
able to interact

00:03:47.230 --> 00:03:49.540 align:middle line:84%
the performers and
emcee so that they

00:03:49.540 --> 00:03:52.710 align:middle line:84%
can receive their award without
leaving their home in England.

00:03:52.710 --> 00:03:54.640 align:middle line:84%
And the audience
had the opportunity

00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:56.600 align:middle line:90%
to see the whole thing.

00:03:56.600 --> 00:04:02.200 align:middle line:84%
So this is an example of how we
are using digital environments

00:04:02.200 --> 00:04:06.070 align:middle line:84%
already, simulations, in
the entertainment world.

00:04:06.070 --> 00:04:09.600 align:middle line:84%
And there's another example,
that was even more recent,

00:04:09.600 --> 00:04:13.150 align:middle line:84%
and this was at the 2014
Billboard Music Awards.

00:04:13.150 --> 00:04:15.700 align:middle line:84%
This one, however,
was very controversial

00:04:15.700 --> 00:04:20.800 align:middle line:84%
because it was a video of
Michael Jackson performing

00:04:20.800 --> 00:04:23.980 align:middle line:84%
a song that had
never been released.

00:04:23.980 --> 00:04:27.970 align:middle line:84%
The problem was Michael
Jackson died in 2009.

00:04:27.970 --> 00:04:31.180 align:middle line:84%
And the simulation that
you're going to see

00:04:31.180 --> 00:04:34.810 align:middle line:84%
is so real that people in
the audience, some of them,

00:04:34.810 --> 00:04:39.550 align:middle line:84%
were actually offended
at the reality

00:04:39.550 --> 00:04:43.760 align:middle line:84%
of having a deceased man perform
in front of them on the screen.

00:04:43.760 --> 00:04:46.990 align:middle line:84%
And the point of me sharing
this with you is the audience

00:04:46.990 --> 00:04:50.410 align:middle line:84%
could not tell that this
was a digital reality,

00:04:50.410 --> 00:04:51.650 align:middle line:90%
it looked so real.

00:04:51.650 --> 00:04:52.450 align:middle line:90%
So here it is.

00:04:52.450 --> 00:04:54.048 align:middle line:10%
You can check it
out for yourself.

